CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 10, 1954, pg. 1 reads: "...James Mitchell, 21, of 2521 Chauncey Drive, another passenger, and Air Force Sgt. William Grossman, 31, who was home on furlough from Brooks Field, San Antonio, Tex., and was operating the auto on the right.  Both Hawthorne and Sergeant Grossman are on the seriously injured lists in different hospitals. - Harris...Photos."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of wrecked Buick driven by Sgt. William Grossman, parked in lot
